Results.ReviewText: I started drinking Blend 37 30 odd years ago when i fell in love and was offered a cup. Alas only the love for Blend 37 lasted the course. Every once in awhile I give someone else ago, often in the nescafe family but I return after a jar. But please nescafe it is becoming harder to find
Results.Title: a blend I have tried to beat but always return to

Results.ReviewText: Unique - a strong and intense taste that I've been drinking for over 30 years - have never found anything to compare.  Not the only coffee I drink (I regularly enjoy Gold Blend), but Blend 37 is a full-bodied, intensely flavoured contrast that is really satisfying.  It reminds me of some of the best coffees that I get in Italy - it's certainly so much better than those at UK high street coffee shops.  It's worth the extra cost - I just wish I could find the 200g jar these days!
Results.Title: Hard to find - worth the search

Results.ReviewText:
I have been buying this for over 23 years,  it's the best with milk and sugar.
I did go over to the Parisseine but that seems to have been taken out of production so I went back to the Blend 37 as this seems the all time best. 

I hope Nescafe do not stop producing this but I am disappointed that they have stopped my second choice as it's nice to have a change of Taste now and again.
Results.Title: Full of Taste

Results.ReviewText: Like most people of a certain age, my gran certainly knows what she likes and what she doesn't. I'd always flirted with different Nescafé blends but my gran was a staunch advocate for Blend 37. Since she made me my first mug I was sold! There's something very unique about Blend 37's aroma and whenever I make a mug myself, I'm always reminded of my lovely gran.
Results.Title: Wonderful Coffee

Results.ReviewText: After buying only Nescafe Blend 37 since it was introduced many years ago, without warning it appears to have been taken from the shelves of all the main supermarkets and my wife and I have been unable to discover why?  We have tried other blends e.g. Gold Blend but Blend 37 suits our tastes like no other. Can you please advise?
Results.Title: Nescafe Blend 37 instant coffee

Results.ReviewText: I was very sceptical at first but I would not go back to other instant coffee after tasting this I am in haven . the special ground coffee is only used at the weekend as I woke all week and really like to enjoy my coffee but this gives me the taste of the ground beans in a jar thanks
Results.Title: Taste is just like roast beans

Results.ReviewText: The only instant coffee for me, since first tasting it around 1950 ! The 2 oz tin with the contents in powder form, not granulated, was referred to as 'high roast' and provided a strong, very satisfying flavour. Now in granulated form in a glass jar, the flavour is as great as ever.
Results.Title: Your Le Mans story explains all

Results.ReviewText:
It´s been my 70 yr old Auntie's favorite for years and she passed on the good taste. 
Beautiful flavors, not too roasted not to bitter, excellent balance i'd say. 

This product should be found in more stores!
Results.Title: A favorite at home and with friends!

Results.ReviewText: Opening a new jar of Blend 37 is one of my most favourite smells ever.  I look forward to that moment every time.  Friends and family always want "one of my coffees" when they visit.  Priceless.  Thank you.
Results.Title: Aroma

Results.ReviewText: I regularly buy this with my usual everyday coffee.  This is my "home from work" daily treat!
Results.Title: Lovely and smooth

Results.ReviewText: Nice robust flavour, wakes me up in the morning! Always been a favourite...
Results.Title: Great Flavour!

Results.ReviewText: I always buy Blend 37 as its been my great friend over a working career
